Thank you for reading the instructions. Get ready start with the 40 rounds of this game.

If you need to take a break, feel free to take one after the end of a round, before continuing to the next one.

Remember, the more money the spider gets, the bigger your bonus will be!

(If, at any point, the space key does not take you to the next page, click once on the text and try again.)

response.Q0: The basic strategy that I used was to first inspect the third nodes. After inspecting the third node, if the value was positive, I would inspect the fifth nodes and choose one with a high positive value. This increased my chances of receiving a high score even if the nodes that I did not inspect had negative values.
response.Q1: I only started devising the strategy that I stated in the above paragraph after approximately the 10th round. Before then, i was clicking on random nodes and moved the spider in a more random fashion.
response.Q2: The timer made it the most difficult as there were a few occasions when I wanted to change my mind, however my indecision in the three seconds meant that I missed my opportunity to inspect a node and therefore had to make uninformed decisions in the form of random guesses.

response.Q0: Yes. I did not initially understand that you were able to inspect multiple nodes before moving the spider. Although I read through the instructions, it would have been helpful if this was demonstrated during the tutorial.
